@NODE Anload

ANLOAD   FileName Alias Start Length Direction

   This command will load an animation in @{" LoadAll " LINK "LoadAll"} mode.
   This mode has the advantage that the animation can be played 
   forward, backward or ping-pong and that it can be edited, i.e.
   cropped, flipped, resized, rotated, etc as well as saved.

   Start  - is the number of the frame to start at

   Length - is the number of frames to load. You can give -1
	    if you want ALL the frames (or as many as possible)
	    to be loaded.

   Direction can be: FORWARD, BACKWARD or PINGPONG

   ex (Gui4Cli):
   > Call gcview ANLOAD DH0:MyFile MyAnim 0 -1 PINGPONG

   In LoadAll mode, animations can also be played faster.

   Note that you can also load the animation normally and then
   load all frames on the fly, by hitting F6 (see shortcuts)

