@NODE CLI_opts

   ToolTypes and Options
--------------------------------------------------------------
   GCView is a programmable viewer, so most preferences can
   be sent to it as commands. It can also recognise several
   ToolTypes and CLI options, however these are limited at
   the moment. 

   The ToolTypes are stored in GCView's icon and are the same
   as the CLI options :

   - FILE,DELAY/N,HIRES/S,LORES/S,LACE/S,MONITOR,VCENTER/S,
     SCROLL/S,POINTER/S

   where :

   FILE    Is the name of the file (no wildcards etc - maybe later..)

   DELAY   How long to show each picture for (default is forever -
           or till the user clicks the right mouse button)

   HIRES
   LORES
   LACE    Are keywords you can give to force the respective modes

   MONITOR With this option you can manually enter the MonitorID you
           want used (see @{" modes " LINK "modes"}). By default, GCView will try to get
           the monitor id that the Workbench is using or use the 
           DEFAULT_MONITOR_ID. This works, so you best leave it alone.

   VCENTER Center pictures vertically. Pictures will always be centered
           horizontally.

   SCROLL  This is not working very well yet. It will scroll larger
           screen pictures whenever you move the mouse. Pictures are
           always scrolled if your pointer reaches the end of the
           screen - this is just more .. whatever..


... more options may be added later..


